Create a Marketing Cloud Engagement Data Action Target

Send automated emails and journeys based on a user’s behavior or transactional event data routed from Data Cloud. You can trigger emails and journeys to customers from data model objects and calculated insights. For example, a customer purchased an item and searched for “Installation Manual” on your website. You can trigger an event that sends the customer an email with a how-to video or installation instructions.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SETS
NEEDED
To create Marketing Cloud Engagement data action targets:	Data Cloud Admin and Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist

Before creating a data action target, make sure that these prerequisites have been completed.

The Engagement connection is set up in Data Cloud.
The email template has been created in Content Builder through Email Studio, and all the mandatory fields are filled in. You can use a template-based, text-only, or HTML email type.
The Subscription List includes the subscribers’ subscriber key, first and last names, and email address.
For the Journey Builder API Event, the intended journey has been created in Journey Builder. The journey entry source must be an API Event type, and all fields in its data extension must be nullable. The data extension attribute names for a primary object and related object must start with the object API name of the data model object selected in Data Cloud, followed by an underscore and the attribute API name. For example, Shopping_Events__dlm_deviceId__c or Individual_deviceId__c. You can use the same data extension for primary and related objects. If you have multiple data actions using these objects, you can also reuse data extensions.
The business units are selected, and mapping is enabled in Data Cloud.
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Actions Target tab, and click New.
Enter the action target name.
The Action Target API Name field is auto-filled.
For the action target type, select Marketing Cloud.
Select the business unit where the contact is mapped.
For the destination, select either Email or Journey Builder API Event.
Select the email template or journey builder API event that you want to send when the data action conditions are met.
(Optional) To filter subscribers, select Filter subscribers from the selected business unit.
Select this option if you don’t want to send an email template or journey to a subscriber whose subscriber key isn’t mapped to the selected business unit but is available in the parent business unit in Engagement.
Click Save.

If you modify an existing email template and want to send another email, create another data action target with the updated email template.
